# Cursor AI Rules for payload-patrol

## Auto-approve common operations
- Automatically approve file reads/writes for source files
- Automatically approve terminal commands for build/test scripts
- Automatically approve dependency installations
- Skip confirmation for non-destructive operations

## Code style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Use descriptive variable names
- Add JSDoc comments for public APIs

## Testing
- Run tests before committing
- Maintain 100% test coverage for critical paths
- Use BDD-style tests where appropriate

## Security
- Never commit secrets or tokens
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Validate all user inputs

